storyInfo: To retrieve 'The Leader', the Dublinn heads begin to massacre anyone who dares to oppose them. Jane stands up against them to save the townsfolk.

attributes.content: 5:57 P.M. \ Rainy
County Hillock, Unoccupied house in the vicinity of District Ten
Hnngh...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: Finally awake, huh?
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Considering the damage your lungs have taken, just breathing is going to hurt like a bitch. You'd better save your air.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: *cough*, *cough*...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: Your abdomen was pretty much torn open... you're in worse shape than I thought. What kept you alive?
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Aha... not that I'm a doctor, but I know a thing or two about the anatomy of this race or that.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: My friend thought you were a Vouivre. You can't blame him for that. He's young. He never saw your ancestors tromping across the world.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Hnnnng—!
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: Simmer down. That wouldn't be good for you.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: I've seen your Arts, and I've taken some precautions. I'm afraid it won't be easy for you to set this house on fire.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Now look at that face there. Feeling a little relieved now that you know you can't fight me?
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: That might be more natural than your instinct to defend yourself—Might be the truer emotion, one from a deeper place in your heart.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: No...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: Sounds like you're mighty friendly with that word.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: You were forced to become someone you don't want to be. I can see that in your pain.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Who's using you? The moneyed ones who just have to stick their hands everywhere? Maybe the shadows in the high tower? Or some thirsty nationalists ready to bring their country back?
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: No, none of those. You're a gang with a puppet for a leader. There's no way you could've put this together in such a short time under Londinium's watchful eyes.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: You... you're a lesser kind of shadow, shoved out onto the stage.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Now does that mean your puppetmaster's of your same blood?
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Stop...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: Stop what? Too scared to even let me talk about him? Or is it her?
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Sure enough. It's not just you. The whole of Victoria... no, the whole world trembles in fear of that one.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: She must be about your age, but she turned the tables on the ones who'd use her, and so quickly too.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: It looks like change is coming sooner than I thought... We'll need to be ready.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: You... Latera...no...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: No need to go guessing at my motives.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: I didn't care who you were when I decided to save you. Now I actually know who you are, but it hasn't changed my mind one bit.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: You... are...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: You're better off not knowing who I am.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: As soon as you're strong enough to move, you'd best skedaddle. And don't ever tell anyone who saved you either.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: I'm not gonna let you die here. That's all you need to know.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Okay... Thank...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: You can thank me later. All I can do right now is remove the infected tissue and stop the bleeding.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: You got run through with the most infectious kind of Active Originium. A heaping helping of Originium granules shot into your circulatory system through those wounds.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: I gave you an inhibitor shot, but I'm afraid that won't be enough to stop crystals from forming in your organs and even on your skin there.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Soon enough, you'll pass out again with a fever. That's a good thing. Then you won't have to deal with the nasty inside-out pain that comes with the acute attack.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: You may cough up blood. I'll try to keep your head up so you don't drown in your own blood vomit.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Ugh.... Mm-hmm...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: And that's just the start of the suffering. You probably can't go back to your old life. Oripathy's writing a whole new course for you.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Your followers will abandon you. Some will hate you, look down on you. It won't be easy for you to lead again, and it'll be hard to get your kin to accept you as you are now.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Hah...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: Oh? There's that face again. That's not despair. No, that's relief, at becoming an Oripathy patient?
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Well, I don't blame you. No matter how intense the artillery barrage, it's never enough to pin down a young red dragon.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: You're looking to dodge destiny, but fighting something like that's gonna come with a hefty price tag.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: I got one thing wrong there—
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: You may be less belligerent than your kin, but you're just as tenacious, and no less courageous.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Ughh...!
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: Relax. Get some sleep. I'll be here.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: It's... too...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: ...dangerous...
attributes.name: Severely Infected

attributes.content: It's dangerous here? That's what you manage to squeeze out before you go dark?
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: It's definitely a little too quiet.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: I'm gonna say you're more than just a pawn to them. Looks like a change of plans.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: This is a risk, but Rhodes Island needs your intel... I'm sure Kal'tsit will understand.
attributes.name: Outcast

attributes.content: Report. We haven't found her.
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: You idiot!
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: What good are you morons when you can't even keep track of one girl?!
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: S-Sorry!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: You're sure she was struck?
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: Yes... One of my sentinels saw it himself. There was an execution this morning when the bombardment happened, The Leader might've...
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: She's our bloody Leader! You understand, don't you?!
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: You remember what you swore when you joined? Now you run with your tail between your legs the moment the enemy shows?!
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: It—It all happened so fast! We didn't have time to respond...
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Besides, The Leader said she wanted some time alone, and ordered to keep everyone away...
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: So what if I tell you to drop dead, you gobshite!
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: And you tell me you're not bloody useless!
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: Stop it. Beating him to a pulp won't do us any good.
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: We just need to know if she's dead or alive, and where she is.
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: Let... me... do it...
attributes.name: 'The Toxicologist'

attributes.content: Alright. Just don't go overboard.
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: *Sigh*...
attributes.name: 'The Toxicologist'

attributes.content: P-Please forgive me... *sobs*... Please...
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: What's... going on... Ugh! Bleuch—
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Hah... hahahaha!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Did you see... her...?
attributes.name: 'The Toxicologist'

attributes.content: She fell! She fell! Hahahahaha! She fell! Got blown up! Dead!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: ...dead...
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: —That's what you call not overboard?
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: I used... too much... Need to... remember this...
attributes.name: 'The Toxicologist'

attributes.content: Well, that's bloody disgusting. Remind me to steer clear of this sick bastard when he tests his drugs out.
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: At least we know he wasn't lying.
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: The blast knocked her out right here, and she was heavily injured. It was most likely fatal.
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: But she couldn't have gone far with that wound. So where is she? It's not like she got blasted clean through the ground!
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: I don't mind blowing up the whole street again.
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: Next time you blow anything up, let people KNOW first!
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: Who said we're blowing up a street?
attributes.name: 'The Accountant'

attributes.content: We need to find her, even if we have to burn down the whole city to do it. One street won't stop us.
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: It's clowns like you, stupid as the Victorian Army, that make holding this city rapidly more trouble than it's worth.
attributes.name: 'The Accountant'

attributes.content: So what do you think we should do?
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: Who takes the fall when The Leader finds out we lost her, huh?
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: The Leader's anger is not the only thing we have to fear.
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: I invite you to think about it. In the eyes of our many warriors and compatriots, she stands for Dublinn.
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: If she breaks free of our control, it won't matter whether our enemies or our ill-meaning 'friends' get their hands on her. It isn't a happy ending.
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: Come to think of it, she... she knows all our bloody plans!
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: Say, those two ladies... do they know about this?
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: They left as soon as the meeting was over. I don't think they would've caught word just yet.
attributes.name: 'The Accountant'

attributes.content: Mandragora's not fond of the girl. She's not going to care.
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: Harmonie... I'm not even sure if she's on our side.
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: Watch your words. We all stand by our Leader.
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: Say what you will, I don't care what you do with Harmonie, but Mandragora's a good girl. Don't you dare drag her down.
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: Why would we, my friend? She's an inseparable part of our team. Like us, she longs to demonstrate her talents and loyalty to the Leader.
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: I've no idea what Harmonie said to Mandragora, or why it has her hanging onto every word. She's too happy to be doing it, too, almost like she expects something.
attributes.name: 'The Accountant'

attributes.content: What's so important about a transmitter that it's worth delaying our victory?
attributes.name: 'The Immolator'

attributes.content: The Leader still hasn't shown any hint of approval toward our plans.
attributes.name: 'The Accountant'

attributes.content: As long as we can prove to her that we've done no wrong, we still have a chance to persuade her yet.
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: So you mean, we still have to look for her?
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: Even if we must search the entire city.
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: Alright. Enough chit-chat, then. Let's move!
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: Wait, wake 'The Convict' up.
attributes.name: 'The Accountant'

attributes.content: Huh? Us five aren't enough to drag her back?
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: Don't forget our agreement. We all will take credit for our achievements.
attributes.name: 'The Accountant'

attributes.content: Get a load of you... You'd sell your own mother.
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: If the idea's to keep the outside from catching wind of this, then what are we doing with these troops?
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: Naturally, we'll bring them with us. After all, the more hands, the better, until we find our quarry.
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: And once we do...?
attributes.name: 'The Bandit'

attributes.content: I'm sure we all know what comes next.
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: No one can escape Dublinn—
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: And no one may ever glimpse its secrets.
attributes.name: 'The Elocutionist'

attributes.content: We need to get rid of these bandages—
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: But I washed them already...
attributes.name: Young Volunteer

attributes.content: That's not going to help. The whole box has been contaminated by the Originium on the ground. We can't be sure the dust's been completely washed off.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Jane, look, I know you're speaking sense, but we don't have enough supplies.
attributes.name: Young Volunteer

attributes.content: Look over there. They're carrying even more people in. Look at how seriously wounded they are...
attributes.name: Young Volunteer

attributes.content: Are those...
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Do you know them?
attributes.name: Young Volunteer

attributes.content: I... yes, I... knew them.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: But I don't think they'd want to see me here.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Could you look after them? I'll head for the clinic and see if I can find some supplies.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Jane, look! Someone's here!
attributes.name: Young Volunteer

attributes.content: Out of the way!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Sir, are you here to help us?
attributes.name: Young Volunteer

attributes.content: Out of the way means out of the way.
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Wait, are you... Ronan?
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: Go block-by-block, and make sure you're thorough! There's a lot of alleys around here, and she could be hiding anywhere! Got it?
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: What are you doing, Ronan? It's us! Your neighbors! You put on new clothes and suddenly you don't know us?
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: I have... an important mission. Piss off, or don't say I didn't warn you!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Craig's hurt. Please, help him. He's helped you out so much...
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: What are you talking about?!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: *Whimpers*... I...
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: (The wounds on her back are serious...)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: (And her kid, Craig... he's had a bad wound to his head too.)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: (I need to stop their bleeding, but I know they don't look kindly on me...)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: You've searched this whole place?
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Are you positive no one here matches her description?
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: (Are they looking for somebody?)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Ugh. No... no. All these people shoving in here, it's a mess. What do we say to the higher-ups if more of them sneak in once we turn and leave?
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: (Are they... looking for the woman Outcast saved?)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: (Does that mean she's in danger...?)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: (I need to go.)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Oi, you lot. Get up, and leave at once!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Sir, we have far too many wounded here. None of them can move...
attributes.name: Young Volunteer

attributes.content: I give no shit you can't move. Get up and go!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: I want all these Oripathics out of this district! Keep an eye out in case they pop. Even the Originium shards outside aren't as dangerous as this lot!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Let's take a fine example. This boy with the bloody face—
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: *Whimpers*... M—Ma...
attributes.name: Craig

attributes.content: Craig, Craig! No, please don't take him! I beg you!
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: You! You're not just abandoning them, you're going to kill them?!
attributes.name: Young Volunteer

attributes.content: What's your bloody problem?! We're Tarans, all of us! What's wrong with a sacrifice for Tara's great cause?!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Ronan, that's what you said last time, and that's when we lost Saoirse!
attributes.name: Angry Youth

attributes.content: (Saoirse...?!)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: (It's him... He's the one who betrayed Saoirse...)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: (And then they took her and... they...)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: (He traded Saoirse's life for that uniform!)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: She deserved it! She betrayed—our—trust!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: That's what you get for failing to understand our great Leader's struggle! And if you don't cooperate, you're next!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Enough.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Jane? I... I thought you'd left?
attributes.name: Young Volunteer

attributes.content: And who do you think you are? Wait, I've seen you before... You're not Taran, are you?
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Please, stop.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: You talk like it sounds so light. Who are you to decide who should sacrifice for anything?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: What's that you're holding... A banner?!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: You... You're a Victorian soldier!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Am I...?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: No, not anymore.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: But. If you insist on trampling the lives of the innocent, then I am your enemy.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Innocent...? Do you know what they've done? You call them innocent?
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: This child, and everyone here... None of them's got clean hands.
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Then... what about you?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: You traded your own people for your position, and now you turn around to oppress them... Who will judge you?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: And who are you standing up all cocksure for? Come on, get her out of here! And round up all the Infected mingling with the Victorian deserter! It's time we clean them up!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Please, help us! Help...
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: That's far enough.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: What are you trying here? Bugger off already!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Look at you carrying that tatty banner wherever you go. You don't have what it takes to be a real soldier, do you?
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Whether that's so, or whether it's not, I will not let you continue doing evil here.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Oh, can you not even cop on? What do they have to do with you? You're going to let them fiddle you like this? Thick as a brick up there, you are!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: True, I can't speak Taran.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: I can't cross my heart and claim I've experienced the life you all have.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: I don't have Oripathy, either.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: But...
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: For the past two years, every day, I've walked the same streets as you.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: I've heard your tears. More than that, I've seen your smiles.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: I know deep down that we are all the same people, living our lives.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: As long as we're human, we will make mistakes. Those who do—should be stopped, and judged. They should be tormented by their own hearts—
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: But. It's not for some ungrateful brute to decide their fates.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: You... You're going to protect us? You don't hate us?
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: *Exhale*... I'd be lying... if I said 'not at all.'
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: I'll stop pretending... there's no bitterness between us. What Craig did was wrong, too, and I've no intention of shielding any guilt.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: But a friend has taught me—the evil I see before me has to be stopped.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: This has nothing to do with which side I'm on. I'm doing what's right.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Th—Thank you...
attributes.name: Sorrowful Woman

attributes.content: Calm down, Craig. You don't need to tug so hard.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: It doesn't matter if I was ever a good soldier. I've been ready to fight from the moment I deserted.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: But your wounds...
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: (Rip—)
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: The banner's the cleanest thing I have on me, and there's a better use for it right now.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Jane gently wraps the torn piece of the banner around the wounded child's forehead.
*Sobs*... I—I'm sorry... M... Miss...
attributes.name: Craig

attributes.content: Don't worry for now, Craig. You get some rest.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: As for you, soldier, it's time you leave—
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: And before you do, you'll need to pay for what you did to Saoirse.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: What, and you'll make me, all by yourself?
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: If I have to.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: ...We're with you too.
attributes.name: Angry Youth

attributes.content: One by one, the wounded men with less serious injuries step out of their hiding spots and stand behind Jane, the girl with her banner held up high.
What... What are you all doing?!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Are you going to resist Dublinn?! O'Brien, you should be helping me get her! Don't forget how Damian died!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: No, Ronan. I haven't forgotten about Damian, but on the other hand... I haven't forgotten about Saoirse either.
attributes.name: Angry Youth

attributes.content: We've done a lot of bad... I'm not blind. Now that it's come to this, I can tell who's really been trying to help us all along.
attributes.name: Angry Youth

attributes.content: She's not even Taran!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Do you see the looks in their eyes?
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: We stand together. For now, at the very least.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: You... absolute idiots! You'll all die here for your foolishness!
attributes.name: Dublinn Soldier

attributes.content: Watch your injuries. Don't push yourselves.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: Leave these villains to me.
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: I will win this battle...
attributes.name: Janie

attributes.content: No—together, we will win this!
attributes.name: Janie
